:::summary
The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints (LDS Church), headquartered in Salt Lake City, Utah, is a Christian faith that believes in the restoration of Christ's original church through the prophet Joseph Smith in 1830. With over 17 million members worldwide, it is one of the fastest-growing religions in the world. Members believe in continuing revelation, additional scripture, and a living prophet who leads the Church today.
:::

